    rawMarkdown: "# Installing GitHub Desktop\r\n\r\n## Step-by-Step Installation Guide\r\n\r\n### For Windows\r\n\r\n1. **Download GitHub Desktop**\r\n   - Go to: https://desktop.github.com/\r\n   - Click the \"Download for Windows\" button\r\n   - Save the installer file\r\n\r\n2. **Run the Installer**\r\n   - Double-click the downloaded file (GitHubDesktopSetup.exe)\r\n   - The installer will automatically install the application\r\n   - GitHub Desktop will launch when installation is complete\r\n\r\n3. **Sign In**\r\n   - When GitHub Desktop opens, you'll see a welcome screen\r\n   - Click \"Sign in to GitHub.com\"\r\n   - Enter your GitHub username and password\r\n   - (If you don't have a GitHub account, click \"Create your free account\")\r\n\r\n4. **Authorize GitHub Desktop**\r\n   - Your browser will open\r\n   - Click \"Authorize Desktop\"\r\n   - Return to GitHub Desktop\r\n\r\n### For Mac\r\n\r\n1. **Download GitHub Desktop**\r\n   - Go to: https://desktop.github.com/\r\n   - Click the \"Download for macOS\" button\r\n   - Save the .zip file\r\n\r\n2. **Install the Application**\r\n   - Open your Downloads folder\r\n   - Double-click the .zip file to extract it\r\n   - Drag GitHub Desktop to your Applications folder\r\n   - Open GitHub Desktop from Applications\r\n\r\n3. **Sign In**\r\n   - When GitHub Desktop opens, you'll see a welcome screen\r\n   - Click \"Sign in to GitHub.com\"\r\n   - Enter your GitHub username and password\r\n   - (If you don't have a GitHub account, click \"Create your free account\")\r\n\r\n4. **Authorize GitHub Desktop**\r\n   - Your browser will open\r\n   - Click \"Authorize Desktop\"\r\n   - Return to GitHub Desktop\r\n\r\n### Creating a GitHub Account (If Needed)\r\n\r\nIf you don't have a GitHub account:\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://github.com/join\r\n2. Enter your email address\r\n3. Create a password\r\n4. Choose a username\r\n5. Verify you're not a robot\r\n6. Click \"Create account\"\r\n7. Verify your email address\r\n\r\n**Username Tips**:\r\n- Choose something professional (you might use this for job applications!)\r\n- Keep it simple and memorable\r\n- You can use your real name or a professional handle\r\n- Examples: john-smith, jsmith-dev, smithcodes\r\n\r\n## System Requirements\r\n\r\n### Windows\r\n- Windows 10 64-bit or later\r\n- 500 MB available disk space\r\n\r\n### Mac\r\n- macOS 10.13 or later\r\n- 500 MB available disk space\r\n\r\n## Troubleshooting Installation\r\n\r\n### Windows Issues\r\n\r\n**Problem**: \"Windows protected your PC\" message\r\n- **Solution**: Click \"More info\" then \"Run anyway\"\r\n\r\n**Problem**: Installation fails\r\n- **Solution**: Make sure you have administrator rights\r\n- Try right-clicking the installer and selecting \"Run as administrator\"\r\n\r\n### Mac Issues\r\n\r\n**Problem**: \"GitHub Desktop can't be opened because it is from an unidentified developer\"\r\n- **Solution**:\r\n  1. Go to System Preferences > Security & Privacy\r\n  2. Click \"Open Anyway\"\r\n  3. Confirm by clicking \"Open\"\r\n\r\n**Problem**: Can't move to Applications folder\r\n- **Solution**: Make sure you have permission to modify Applications folder\r\n\r\n## Verifying Installation\r\n\r\nAfter installation, you should see:\r\n\r\n1. âœ… GitHub Desktop application is open\r\n2. âœ… You're signed in with your GitHub account\r\n3. âœ… You see the main GitHub Desktop interface\r\n\r\n## What's Installed?\r\n\r\nGitHub Desktop includes:\r\n\r\n- **The GitHub Desktop app** - The main application\r\n- **Git** - The version control system (installed automatically)\r\n- **Command line tools** - For advanced users (optional)\r\n\r\n## Alternative: Using GitHub Desktop Without an Account\r\n\r\nYou can use GitHub Desktop without a GitHub.com account, but you'll miss out on:\r\n- Backing up your code to the cloud\r\n- Collaborating with others\r\n- Showcasing your projects publicly\r\n\r\n**Recommendation**: Create a free GitHub account - it's worth it!\r\n\r\n## Next Steps\r\n\r\nNow that GitHub Desktop is installed, let's configure it!\r\n\r\nğŸ‘‰ **Next**: `initial-setup.md`\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Quick Links\r\n\r\n- GitHub Desktop Website: https://desktop.github.com/\r\n- GitHub Desktop Documentation: https://docs.github.com/en/desktop\r\n- GitHub Help: https://support.github.com/\r\n",
